{"type":"message","id":"43ca0e98","parentId":"c132d5d5","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:44:56.707Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_PZUDdr4LhcTr8q4tjovbdQFL","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ACTIVE_TASK_TEMPLATE.md\n\nStatus: active\nPriority: P1\nStarted: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM\nUpdated: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM\nWorkspace: /absolute/path\nOwner: main-session\nUser Trigger: original user instruction\nResume Entry: first file/report/command to reopen\n\n## Goal\n- One-sentence definition of the task to finish\n\n## Acceptance\n- Deliverable or proof 1\n- Deliverable or proof 2\n\n## Current\n- Exactly one item being executed now\n\n## Next\n- Next pending item\n- Next pending item after that\n\n## Completed\n- [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] Finished item + proof\n\n## Evidence\n- /absolute/path/to/file\n- command + key output summary\n\n## Blockers\n- None\n\n## Rules\n- `Current` must contain exactly one active item.\n- After finishing `Current`, move it to `Completed`, add proof under `Evidence`, then promote the first item in `Next` into `Current`.\n- Prefer rewriting the whole file once instead of chaining multiple partial edits.\n- After each write, read the file back and verify `Current`, `Next`, and `Completed` before reporting the new state.\n- If prompt context reports `Integrity Warnings`, repair the file before claiming the task state changed.\n- Only set `Status: blocked` when the blocker is real and specific.\n- Only set `Status: done` when `Acceptance` is met.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774082696698}}
{"type":"message","id":"4af82598","parentId":"43ca0e98","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:45:41.187Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning project integration**\n\nI’m considering how to integrate the architecture and signal generator into the existing system. The user's phrase “从零实现” indicates a direct instruction to start, so I’ll create an ACTIVE_TASK. I think I need to deliver something tangible, like a design spec or implementation plan. Perhaps I can draft a document as a fusion blueprint, then also start scaffolding the script. It seems there's an expectation to begin actual coding, so I’ll also create a skeleton script and a strategy config module.**Starting system implementation**\n\nI'm realizing that implementing the entire strategy from scratch is quite a big task. I can kick things off by creating a skeleton script, like `scripts/generate_day13_mean_reversion_signals.py`, along with a config file. The user asked for implementation from scratch, so I’ll proceed accordingly without further questions. I'll need to inspect the repository for existing scripts and coding patterns to integrate smoothly. If there's an ACTIVE_TASK, I’ll overwrite it if priorities change. After that, I’ll verify by reading back and showing the progress.**Planning for commits**\n\nI need to consider committing changes eventually, but I might not need to do it all in one go. The developer suggests I commit after making edits. If I make any file changes now, I'll commit at the end of this turn. However, I should only commit if I actually made modifications. Since the workspace is cluttered with existing changes, I'll need to ensure I get the exact hash from the git output; that may be a bit tricky!**Considering git workflow**\n\nI’m thinking about how to avoid committing the entire tree when using git. It seems like using git add to specify only new files would be the way to go, especially to avoid unrelated changes. I could check the status first, then add specific files, like checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md, and follow up with a commit. However, I'm also unsure if I need to commit every change right now. Maybe I can explore using a subagent for more complex tasks, but that might complicate things further.**Exploring implementation strategies**\n\nIt seems I might need immediate evidence, so spawning a subagent could help. If I do that, I have to yield for results, but the user expects an answer right away. Maybe I can start a subagent and mention it’s running, but I also need to consider artifacts as proof. It might be better to create a plan file for clarity and take direct action. I should analyze target scripts, potentially create a new folder or script, and start with my goal: implementing a signal script that integrates and tests effectively.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kJsdB7s4Y2yS40IOMCYIoa6i","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md","content":"Status: active\nPriority: P1\nStarted: 2026-03-21 16:46\nUpdated: 2026-03-21 16:46\nWorkspace: /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\nOwner: main-session\nUser Trigger: 张玲要求基于小红书 day1-3 思路，在 personal-a-share-research-system 中从零实现可融合的均值回归/超跌反弹策略\nResume Entry: /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system\n\n## Goal\n- 从零实现 day1-3 风格的 A 股日频均值回归信号模块，并接入现有 personal-a-share-research-system 的信号/回测链路\n\n## Acceptance\n- 产出新的策略说明或配置文件，明确 day1-3 信号规则、市场状态门控与接入方式\n- 产出至少一个可运行脚本，能生成标准化 `date,instrument,score` 信号文件或直接进入现有回测链路\n- 产出一次最小验收结果（脚本运行输出、报告或日志），证明首版实现已能被系统读取/验证\n\n## Current\n- 梳理现有接入点并落地首版 day1-3 信号脚本骨架\n\n## Next\n- 补充 day1-3 配置文件与字段约定，使其可被现有系统参数化调用\n- 跑一次最小样本或 smoke test，生成结果文件并评估下一轮需要补强的规则\n\n## Completed\n- [2026-03-21 16:42] 完成 day1-3 与现有量化系统的融合可行性分析，确认以信号层接入最合适\n\n## Evidence\n- 小红书笔记解析：day1-3 已实现日频均值回归/超跌反弹策略、市场状态 strong/neutral/weak 门控、T 日决策/T+1 成交回测\n- /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config/rd_agent_integration.yaml\n- /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_rd_agent_factor_overlay_backtest.py\n\n## Blockers\n- None\n\n## Rules\n- `Current` must contain exactly one active item.\n- After finishing `Current`, move it to `Completed`, add proof under `Evidence`, then promote the first item in `Next` into `Current`.\n- Prefer rewriting the whole file once instead of chaining multiple partial edits.\n- After each write, read the file back and verify `Current`, `Next`, and `Completed` before reporting the new state.\n- If prompt context reports `Integrity Warnings`, repair the file before claiming the task state changed.\n- Only set `Status: blocked` when the blocker is real and specific.\n- Only set `Status: done` when `Acceptance` is met.\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774082696709}}
