{"type":"message","id":"96a95a67","parentId":"a1ce9676","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:47:03.303Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Continuing implementation tasks**\n\nI need to continue implementing by editing files and running tests. It looks like I’ll also create a config and script. I want to inspect the repository structure and documents to ensure everything is clear. A minimal deliverable seems best, and perhaps direct edits might be easier than using a subagent. I'm planning to craft a signal script based on the data from days 1 to 3 and understand the standardized signal format. I might create a configuration file and a candidate generator script, along with an export script. It seems necessary to run a smoke test and inspect backtest scripts too.**Implementing day 1-3 features**\n\nI'm looking to implement the features from the day 1-3 summary using HS300 trends combined with market breadth indicators. I'll focus on oversold rebound features from metrics like MA deviation and relative returns. It sounds like I might need to set up a way to choose a universe directory and utilize qbot_ashare processed CSVs for output.\n\nI’ll consider performance, but doing a smoke test with about 100 files should be fine for now. I'll also explore including a max-symbol option and draft both a candidate CSV and a standardized raw signal output.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cV4WEdSvD2qMo7mn1RpeM4eK","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config/rd_agent_integration.yaml"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ESekNmInk6CoI38q1bjGRuvP","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/processed/rd_agent/factor_signal_template.csv')\nprint(p.exists())\nif p.exists():\n import pandas as pd\n df=pd.read_csv(p