{"type":"message","id":"555c2e68","parentId":"25553ac3","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:49:22.392Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning implementation steps**\n\nI need to respond to the user, likely asking me to move forward with zero implementation. We've created ACTIVE_TASK and now I need to continue producing evidence in the same turn. I might actually have to implement some files and run a smoke test, updating the ACTIVE_TASK with CLI advancements, and then commit changes. However, the repo has a lot of unrelated changes, so I'll need to be selective in my commits. I'd like to implement a minimal generator script, possibly update rd_agent_integration, and really focus on producing actual evidence for the user.**Planning the new script**\n\nI need to inspect relevant existing scripts to see if generate live_smallcap_candidates can be adapted. To save time, I might implement a new script from scratch using price data and daily_basic for turnover analysis. Creating a config YAML with mean reversion parameters and output paths is also on my list. I want to generate RD CSVs with the necessary fields for the risk engine. Including market state gates based on the HS300 trend and other metrics is essential too. For the smoke test, I may run it over the last trade date using chunking to manage the 731MB data file effectively.**Developing initial implementation**\n\nSince the user wants to implement the fusion from scratch, I think it might be enough to deliver a first version focused on latest-day signal generation, rather than a complete backtest. The acceptance criteria mention needing at least one runnable script that generates a standardized signal file or enters a chaining process, including a smoke test. I’ll need to inspect the expected raw signal format for merging and applying risk to signals. I should also check the output columns, like trade_date, ts_code, and others from export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_SlgF7OOEyc9xvdr3XidiV17y","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774082946128}}
{"type":"message","id":"fab39de5","parentId":"555c2e68","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:49:22.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_SlgF7OOEyc9xvdr3XidiV17y","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Export normalized signal file for smallcap_chip_v4_2_alpha_recover.\n\n当前为主系统接入的第一版适配器：\n- 输入：人工/研究侧整理好的候选列表 CSV\n- 输出：标准化 signal CSV 到 signals/raw/\n\n输入 CSV 最低要求字段：\n- ts_code（或 code / symbol）\n可选字段：\n- score\n- target_weight\n- comment\n\n示例：\npython3 scripts/export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py \\\n  --input research/reports/manual_smallcap_candidates_20260310.csv \\\n  --trade-date 2026-03-10\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport pandas as pd\n\n\nSTRATEGY_ID = \"smallcap_chip_v4_2\"\n\n\ndef normalize_code(value: str) -> str:\n    v = str(value).strip()\n    if v.endswith((\".SZ\", \".SH\", \".BJ\")):\n        return v\n    if v.startswith((\"60\", \"68\")):\n        return f\"{v}.SH\"\n    if v.startswith((\"00\", \"30\")):\n        return f\"{v}.SZ\"\n    if v.startswith((\"8\", \"4\")):\n        return f\"{v}.BJ\"\n    return v\n\n\ndef resolve_code_column(df: pd.DataFrame) -> str:\n    for col in [\"ts_code\", \"code\", \"symbol\"]:\n        if col in df.columns:\n            return col\n    raise ValueError(\"Input CSV must contain one of: ts_code, code, symbol\")\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    ap.add_argument(\"--input\", required=True, help=\"candidate csv path\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--trade-date\", required=True, help=\"trade date, e.g. 2026-03-10\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--output\", default=None, help=\"output path; default signals/raw/{strategy_id}_{trade_date}.csv\")\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"input file not found: {input_path}\")\n\n    df = pd.read_csv(input_path)\n    code_col = resolve_code_column(df)\n\n    out = pd.DataFrame()\n    out[\"trade_date\"] = [args.trade_date] * len(df)\n    out[\"ts_code\"] = df[code_col].map(normalize_code)\n    out[\"signal_type\"] = \"BUY\"\n    out[\"score\"] = df[\"score\"] if \"score\" in df.columns else 1.0\n    out[\"target_weight\"] = df[\"target_weight\"] if \"target_weight\" in df.columns else None\n    out[\"strategy_id\"] = STRATEGY_ID\n    out[\"risk_flag\"] = \"normal\"\n    out[\"comment\"] = df[\"comment\"] if \"comment\" in df.columns else \"exported_from_candidate_list\"\n    out[\"source_run_id\"] = f\"{STRATEGY_ID}_{args.trade_date.replace('-', '')}\"\n    out[\"generated_at\"] = datetime.now().astimezone().isoformat()\n\n    out = out.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"trade_date\", \"ts_code\", \"strategy_id\"], keep=\"last\")\n\n    if args.output:\n        output_path = Path(args.output)\n    else:\n        base = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n        output_path = base / \"signals\" / \"raw\" / f\"{STRATEGY_ID}_{args.trade_date.replace('-', '')}.csv\"\n\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    out.to_csv(output_path, index=False)\n    print(f\"wrote {len(out)} rows -> {output_path}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Export normalized signal file for smallcap_chip_v4_2_alpha_recover.\n\n当前为主系统接入的第一版适配器：\n- 输入：人工/研究侧整理好的候选列表 CSV\n- 输出：标准化 signal CSV 到 signals/raw/\n\n输入 CSV 最低要求字段：\n- ts_code（或 code / symbol）\n可选字段：\n- score\n- target_weight\n- comment\n\n示例：\npython3 scripts/export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py \\\n  --input research/reports/manual_smallcap_candidates_20260310.csv \\\n  --trade-date 2026-03-10\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport pandas as pd\n\n\nSTRATEGY_ID = \"smallcap_chip_v4_2\"\n\n\ndef normalize_code(value: str) -> str:\n    v = str(value).strip()\n    if v.endswith((\".SZ\", \".SH\", \".BJ\")):\n        return v\n    if v.startswith((\"60\", \"68\")):\n        return f\"{v}.SH\"\n    if v.startswith((\"00\", \"30\")):\n        return f\"{v}.SZ\"\n    if v.startswith((\"8\", \"4\")):\n        return f\"{v}.BJ\"\n    return v\n\n\ndef resolve_code_column(df: pd.DataFrame) -> str:\n    for col in [\"ts_code\", \"code\", \"symbol\"]:\n        if col in df.columns:\n            return col\n    raise ValueError(\"Input CSV must contain one of: ts_code, code, symbol\")\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    ap.add_argument(\"--input\", required=True, help=\"candidate csv path\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--trade-date\", required=True, help=\"trade date, e.g. 2026-03-10\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--output\", default=None, help=\"output path; default signals/raw/{strategy_id}_{trade_date}.csv\")\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"input file not found: {input_path}\")\n\n    df = pd.read_csv(input_path)\n    code_col = resolve_code_column(df)\n\n    out = pd.DataFrame()\n    out[\"trade_date\"] = [args.trade_date] * len(df)\n    out[\"ts_code\"] = df[code_col].map(normalize_code)\n    out[\"signal_type\"] = \"BUY\"\n    out[\"score\"] = df[\"score\"] if \"score\" in df.columns else 1.0\n    out[\"target_weight\"] = df[\"target_weight\"] if \"target_weight\" in df.columns else None\n    out[\"strategy_id\"] = STRATEGY_ID\n    out[\"risk_flag\"] = \"normal\"\n    out[\"comment\"] = df[\"comment\"] if \"comment\" in df.columns else \"exported_from_candidate_list\"\n    out[\"source_run_id\"] = f\"{STRATEGY_ID}_{args.trade_date.replace('-', '')}\"\n    out[\"generated_at\"] = datetime.now().astimezone().isoformat()\n\n    out = out.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"trade_date\", \"ts_code\", \"strategy_id\"], keep=\"last\")\n\n    if args.output:\n        output_path = Path(args.output)\n    else:\n        base = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n        output_path = base / \"signals\" / \"raw\" / f\"{STRATEGY_ID}_{args.trade_date.replace('-', '')}.csv\"\n\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    out.to_csv(output_path, index=False)\n    print(f\"wrote {len(out)} rows -> {output_path}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774082962468}}
{"type":"message","id":"b32bb005","parentId":"fab39de5","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:49:33.855Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning data tasks**\n\nI’m thinking about producing the rd_agent CSV and the raw signal CSV. After that, I need to run a smoke test to generate outputs in research/reports and signals/raw, and then update the active task. I also might need to write documentation or a report in Markdown. I should inspect the a_stock_history format and daily_basic as well. There’s a possibility of creating a market breadth gate by computing breadth from index returns. Keeping it simple is key! I’ll look at the existing smallcap candidate script for useful logic and configuration to borrow.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kGxjpkJqBzrQa3DzlSq8OMyH","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_live_smallcap_candidates.py","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_o39Gtqddocm9GdmumS1ykw5Y","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/smallcap_candidate_promotion_20260314.md","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774082962481}}
{"type":"message","id":"79d7c8ed","parentId":"b32bb005","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:49:33.929Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_kGxjpkJqBzrQa3DzlSq8OMyH","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport yaml\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDEFAULT_PRICE_CSV = Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/data/a_stock_history.csv\")\nDEFAULT_BASIC_CSV = PROJECT_ROOT / \"data\" / \"daily_basic_all_2019_2026.csv\"\nDEFAULT_CONFIG = PROJECT_ROOT / \"config\" / \"strategy_smallcap_chip_candidate_top50.yaml\"\n\n\ndef count_csv_rows(path: Path) -> int:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return 0\n    try:\n        with path.open(\"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\", newline=\"\") as handle:\n            return max(0, sum(1 for _ in handle) - 1)\n    except Exception:\n        return 0\n\n\ndef ensure_parent(path: Path) -> None:\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n\ndef load_smallcap_config(path: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return {}\n    payload = yaml.safe_load(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")) or {}\n    return payload.get(\"smallcap_chip\", payload)\n\n\ndef pick_liquid_symbols(frame: pd.DataFrame, max_symbols: int) -> list[str]:\n    latest_dates = sorted(frame[\"date\"].dropna().unique())\n    if not latest_dates:\n        return []\n    cutoff = latest_dates[max(0, len(latest_dates) - 60)]\n    recent = frame[frame[\"date\"] >= cutoff]\n    ranked = (\n        recent.groupby(\"ts_code\", as_index=False)[\"amount\"]\n        .mean()\n        .sort_values(\"amount\", ascending=False)\n        .head(max_symbols)\n    )\n    return sorted(ranked[\"ts_code\"].astype(str).tolist())\n\n\ndef safe_percentile(series: pd.Series, *, ascending: bool = True, fill_value: float = 0.0) -> pd.Series:\n    numeric = pd.to_numeric(series, errors=\"coerce\")\n    ranked = numeric.rank(pct=True, ascending=ascending)\n    return ranked.fillna(fill_value)\n\n\ndef load_price_history(path: Path, target_date: int) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    if not path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(path)\n\n    frame = pd.read_csv(\n        path,\n        usecols=[\"ts_code\", \"trade_date\", \"close\", \"vol\", \"amount\"],\n    )\n    frame[\"trade_date\"] = pd.to_numeric(frame[\"trade_date\"], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0).astype(int)\n    frame = frame[frame[\"trade_date\"] <= target_date].copy()\n    if frame.empty:\n        raise ValueError(f\"no_price_history_le_{target_date}\")\n\n    frame[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(frame[\"trade_date\"].astype(str), format=\"%Y%m%d\", errors=\"coerce\")\n    frame = frame.dropna(subset=[\"date\"]).copy()\n    if frame.empty:\n        raise ValueError(\"no_valid_price_dates\")\n\n    frame[\"ts_code\"] = frame[\"ts_code\"].astype(str).str.upper().str.strip()\n    frame[\"close\"] = pd.to_numeric(frame[\"close\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    frame[\"amount\"] = pd.to_numeric(frame[\"amount\"], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0) * 1000.0\n    frame[\"volume\"] = pd.to_numeric(frame[\"vol\"], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0) * 100.0\n    frame = frame.dropna(subset=[\"ts_code\", \"close\"]).copy()\n    if frame.empty:\n        raise ValueError(\"no_valid_price_rows\")\n    return frame\n\n\ndef build_market_snapshot(frame: pd.DataFrame, cfg: dict[str, Any]) -> tuple[pd.DataFrame, str]:\n    max_symbols = int(cfg.get(\"max_symbols\", 300))\n    smallcap_pct = float(cfg.get(\"smallcap_pct\", 0.35))\n    min_turnover_20d = float(cfg.get(\"min_turnover_20d\", 30_000_000))\n    w_m20 = float(cfg.get(\"w_m20\", 0.55))\n    w_m60 = float(cfg.get(\"w_m60\", 0.45))\n    w_break = float(cfg.get(\"w_break\", 0.25))\n    w_near = float(cfg.get(\"w_near\", 0.05))\n    chip_near_threshold = float(cfg.get(\"chip_near_threshold\", 0.07))\n    volume_break_ratio = float(cfg.get(\"volume_break_ratio\", 1.3))\n\n    selected = pick_liquid_symbols(frame, max_symbols=max_symbols)\n    scoped = frame[frame[\"ts_code\"].isin(selected)].copy()\n    if scoped.empty:\n        raise ValueError(\"liquid_universe_empty\")\n\n    close = scoped.pivot(index=\"date\", columns=\"ts_code\", values=\"close\").sort_index()\n    amount = scoped.pivot(index=\"date\", columns=\"ts_code\", values=\"amount\").sort_index()\n    volume = scoped.pivot(index=\"date\", columns=\"ts_code\", values=\"volume\").sort_index()\n    if close.empty:\n        raise ValueError(\"pivot_close_empty\")\n\n    latest_date = close.index[-1]\n    latest_close = close.loc[latest_date]\n    prev_close = close.shift(1).loc[latest_date]\n    mom20 = close.pct_change(20, fill_method=None).loc[latest_date]\n    mom60 = close.pct_change(60, fill_method=None).loc[latest_date]\n    liq20 = amount.rolling(20).mean().loc[latest_date]\n\n    vwap60_full = (close * volume).rolling(60).sum() / volume.rolling(60).sum().replace(0, np.nan)\n    vwap60 = vwap60_full.loc[latest_date]\n    prev_vwap60 = vwap60_full.shift(1).loc[latest_date]\n    vol_ma20 = volume.rolling(20).mean().loc[latest_date]\n    latest_volume = volume.loc[latest_date]\n\n    chip_break = (\n        (latest_close > vwap60)\n        & (prev_close <= prev_vwap60)\n        & (latest_volume > volume_break_ratio * vol_ma20)\n    ).fillna(False)\n    chip_near = (((latest_close - vwap60).abs() / vwap60.replace(0, np.nan)) <= chip_near_threshold).fillna(False)\n\n    eligible = mom20.notna() & mom60.notna() & liq20.notna() & (liq20 >= min_turnover_20d)\n    eligible_codes = eligible[eligible].index.tolist()\n    if not eligible_codes:\n        raise ValueError(\"eligible_universe_empty\")\n\n    m20_rank = safe_percentile(mom20[eligible_codes], ascending=True)\n    m60_rank = safe_percentile(mom60[eligible_codes], ascending=True)\n    liq_rank = safe_percentile(liq20[eligible_codes], ascending=True)\n    smallcap_mask = liq_rank <= smallcap_pct\n\n    tech_score = (\n        w_m20 * m20_rank\n        + w_m60 * m60_rank\n        + w_break * chip_break[eligible_codes].astype(float)\n        + w_near * chip_near[eligible_codes].astype(float)\n    )\n    tech_score = tech_score[smallcap_mask].sort_values(ascending=False)\n    if tech_score.empty:\n        raise ValueError(\"tech_score_empty_after_smallcap_filter\")\n\n    universe = pd.DataFrame({\"ts_code\": tech_score.index, \"tech_score\": tech_score.values})\n    universe[\"close\"] = pd.to_numeric(latest_close.reindex(universe[\"ts_code\"]).values, errors=\"coerce\")\n    universe[\"mom20\"] = pd.to_numeric(mom20.reindex(universe[\"ts_code\"]).values, errors=\"coerce\")\n    universe[\"mom60\"] = pd.to_numeric(mom60.reindex(universe[\"ts_code\"]).values, errors=\"coerce\")\n    universe[\"liq20\"] = pd.to_numeric(liq20.reindex(universe[\"ts_code\"]).values, errors=\"coerce\")\n    universe[\"vwap60\"] = pd.to_numeric(vwap60.reindex(universe[\"ts_code\"]).values, errors=\"coerce\")\n    universe[\"volume_break\"] = chip_break.reindex(universe[\"ts_code\"]).fillna(False).astype(bool).values\n    universe[\"chip_near\"] = chip_near.reindex(universe[\"ts_code\"]).fillna(False).astype(bool).values\n    universe[\"tech_rank\"] = safe_percentile(universe[\"tech_score\"], ascending=True)\n    universe[\"source_trade_date\"] = latest_date.strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\n    universe = universe.sort_values([\"tech_score\", \"ts_code\"], ascending=[False, True]).reset_index(drop=True)\n    return universe, latest_date.strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\n\n\ndef load_latest_daily_basic(path: Path, target_date: int) -> tuple[str, pd.DataFrame]:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return \"\", pd.DataFrame()\n\n    frame = pd.read_csv(\n        path,\n        usecols=[\"ts_code\", \"trade_date\", \"total_mv\", \"circ_mv\", \"turnover_rate\", \"pe\", \"pb\", \"ps\"],\n    )\n    frame[\"trade_date\"] = pd.to_numeric(frame[\"trade_date\"], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0).astype(int)\n    frame = frame[frame[\"trade_date\"] <= target_date].copy()\n    if frame.empty:\n        return \"\", pd.DataFrame()\n\n    latest_trade_date = int(frame[\"trade_date\"].max())\n    frame = frame[frame[\"trade_date\"] == latest_trade_date].copy()\n    frame[\"ts_code\"] = frame[\"ts_code\"].astype(str).str.upper().str.strip()\n    for col in [\"total_mv\", \"circ_mv\", \"turnover_rate\", \"pe\", \"pb\", \"ps\"]:\n        frame[col] = pd.to_numeric(frame[col], errors=\"coerce\")\n    return str(latest_trade_date), frame\n\n\ndef select_main_candidates(\n    universe: pd.DataFrame,\n    *,\n    limit: int,\n    target_weight: float,\n) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    picked = universe.head(limit).copy()\n    picked[\"score\"] = picked[\"tech_score\"].round(6)\n    picked[\"target_weight\"] = round(float(target_weight), 4)\n    picked[\"comment\"] = \"auto_live_v4_2\"\n    return picked[\n        [\n            \"ts_code\",\n            \"score\",\n            \"target_weight\",\n            \"comment\",\n            \"source_trade_date\",\n            \"close\",\n            \"mom20\",\n            \"mom60\",\n            \"liq20\",\n            \"vwap60\",\n            \"volume_break\",\n            \"chip_near\",\n            \"tech_score\",\n        ]\n    ].copy()\n\n\ndef build_guard_candidates(\n    universe: pd.DataFrame,\n    daily_basic: pd.DataFrame,\n    *,\n    limit: int,\n    target_weight: float,\n) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    merged = universe.merge(\n        daily_basic[[\"ts_code\", \"turnover_rate\", \"pe\", \"pb\", \"ps\", \"total_mv\", \"circ_mv\"]],\n        on=\"ts_code\",\n        how=\"left\",\n    )\n    merged[\"guard_mode\"] = \"fundamental_guard\"\n\n    valid = merged[\n        (pd.to_numeric(merged[\"turnover_rate\"], errors=\"coerce\") >= 0.8)\n        & (pd.to_numeric(merged[\"pb\"], errors=\"coerce\") > 0)\n        & (pd.to_numeric(merged[\"ps\"], errors=\"coerce\") > 0)\n    ].copy()\n\n    if valid.empty:\n        fallback = universe.head(limit).copy()\n        fallback[\"score\"] = fallback[\"tech_score\"].round(6)\n        fallback[\"target_weight\"] = round(float(target_weight), 4)\n        fallback[\"comment\"] = \"auto_live_v4_2b_tech_fallback\"\n        fallback[\"guard_mode\"] = \"tech_fallback_no_basic\"\n        for col in [\"turnover_rate\", \"pe\", \"pb\", \"ps\", \"total_mv\", \"circ_mv\", \"guard_score\"]:\n            fallback[col] = np.nan\n        return fallback[\n            [\n                \"ts_code\",\n                \"score\",\n                \"target_weight\",\n                \"comment\",\n                \"guard_mode\",\n                \"source_trade_date\",\n                \"tech_score\",\n                \"guard_score\",\n                \"turnover_rate\",\n                \"pe\",\n                \"pb\",\n                \"ps\",\n                \"total_mv\",\n                \"circ_mv\","}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport yaml\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDEFAULT_PRICE_CSV = Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/data/a_stock_history.csv\")\nDEFAULT_BASIC_CSV = PROJECT_ROOT / \"data\" / \"daily_basic_all_2019_2026.csv\"\nDEFAULT_CONFIG = PROJECT_ROOT / \"config\" / \"strategy_smallcap_chip_candidate_top50.yaml\"\n\n\ndef count_csv_rows(path: Path) -> int:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return 0\n    try:\n        with path.open(\"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\", newline=\"\") as handle:\n            return max(0, sum(1 for _ in handle) - 1)\n    except Exception:\n        return 0\n\n\ndef ensure_parent(path: Path) -> None:\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=