{"type":"message","id":"67479c8a","parentId":"d43cd1c6","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:53:07.954Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing market conditions**\n\nI'm looking at some market indicators and noticing that we’re near a 10-day low, with a 1-day rebound that's positive. I should consider combining oversold ranks and a bottom bonus to evaluate potential opportunities. Then there's the market gate: it could be considered strong if the HS300 is above the 20-day moving average and the 60-day moving average, or if the closing price is above the 20-day with breadth above a certain threshold.**Planning task execution**\n\nI’m working on how to manage tasks efficiently. After finishing the current item, I need to start the next one in the queue. If the user doesn't have time, I should still aim to make progress. I think adding a markdown report summarizing everything, like the implementation and smoke test, would be a valuable deliverable. I'll update the current task to something specific and perform a smoke test to check everything. I need to inspect the expectations for inputs to ensure everything aligns properly.**Examining test outputs**\n\nI’m considering creating a single-day file to confirm that the script outputs are correct. For the smoke test, I want to ensure that both the rd_agent CSV and the raw signal CSV are produced. The acceptance criteria state that I need to demonstrate the first version can be read and verified by the system. I might also look into running the apply_risk_to_signals function, especially since it's based on one day's raw signal. I'll need to inspect the interface for this function for clarity.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"我先把首版实现直接做出来，并跑一轮最小验收：配置文件、信号生成脚本、原始信号导出和 smoke test 一起落地。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dTELepCybItAjiftEfHtrDge","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/apply_risk_to_signals.py","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_mayH6C4lhchg0h9zyzuF9C5Q","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,260p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_live_signal_tickets.py","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774083145710}}
{"type":"message","id":"883b1262","parentId":"67479c8a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:53:08.040Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_dTELepCybItAjiftEfHtrDge","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Apply risk engine to raw signals and emit approved signals + proposed orders.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport pandas as pd\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nif str(PROJECT_ROOT) not in sys.path:\n    sys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT))\n\nfrom risk.risk_engine import RiskConfig, RiskContext, RiskEngine\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    ap.add_argument(\"--input\", required=True, help=\"raw signal csv\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--trade-date\", required=True)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--account-nav\", type=float, default=1000000)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--available-cash\", type=float, default=1000000)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--market-breadth\", type=float, default=None)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--index-ret-pct\", type=float, default=None)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--strategy-max-dd-pct\", type=float, default=None)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--strategy-sharpe\", type=float, default=None)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--risk-off\", action=\"store_true\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--hard-stop\", action=\"store_true\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--risk-config\", type=str, default=None, help=\"path to risk config JSON\")\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    base = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(input_path)\n\n    raw = pd.read_csv(input_path)\n\n    if args.risk_config:\n        import json\n        with open(args.risk_config) as f:\n            cfg = json.load(f)\n        risk_config = RiskConfig(\n            max_total_exposure=cfg.get(\"max_total_exposure\", 1.0),\n            max_single_weight=cfg.get(\"max_single_weight\", 0.10),\n            riskoff_total_exposure=cfg.get(\"riskoff_total_exposure\", 0.65),\n            hard_stop_enabled=cfg.get(\"hard_stop_enabled\", True),\n            allow_new_buy_when_riskoff=cfg.get(\"allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\", False),\n            max_order_to_adv20_ratio=cfg.get(\"max_order_to_adv20_ratio\", 0.02),\n            index_halt_threshold_pct=cfg.get(\"index_halt_threshold_pct\"),\n            market_breadth_riskoff_threshold=cfg.get(\"market_breadth_riskoff_threshold\"),\n            market_breadth_hard_stop_threshold=cfg.get(\"market_breadth_hard_stop_threshold\"),\n            strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct=cfg.get(\"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\"),\n            strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold=cfg.get(\"strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold\"),\n            style_rotation_enabled=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_enabled\", False),\n            style_rotation_riskoff_short_excess_pct=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_riskoff_short_excess_pct\"),\n            style_rotation_riskoff_medium_excess_pct=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_riskoff_medium_excess_pct\"),\n            style_rotation_hard_stop_short_excess_pct=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_hard_stop_short_excess_pct\"),\n            style_rotation_hard_stop_medium_excess_pct=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_hard_stop_medium_excess_pct\"),\n            style_rotation_hard_stop_requires_negative_smallcap=cfg.get(\n                \"style_rotation_hard_stop_requires_negative_smallcap\",\n                True,\n            ),\n            blocked_codes=cfg.get(\"blocked_codes\", []),\n        )\n    else:\n        risk_config = RiskConfig(\n            max_total_exposure=1.0,\n            max_single_weight=0.10,\n            riskoff_total_exposure=0.65,\n            allow_new_buy_when_riskoff=False,\n        )\n\n    engine = RiskEngine(risk_config)\n    context = RiskContext(\n        trade_date=args.trade_date,\n        market_breadth=args.market_breadth,\n        risk_off=args.risk_off,\n        hard_stop=args.hard_stop,\n        available_cash=args.available_cash,\n        account_nav=args.account_nav,\n        index_ret_pct=args.index_ret_pct,\n        strategy_max_drawdown_pct=args.strategy_max_dd_pct,\n        strategy_sharpe=args.strategy_sharpe,\n    )\n\n    approved = engine.apply(raw, context)\n\n    trade_tag = args.trade_date.replace(\"-\", \"\")\n    approved_path = base / \"signals\" / \"approved\" / f\"approved_signals_{trade_tag}.csv\"\n    approved_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    approved.to_csv(approved_path, index=False)\n\n    # convert to proposed orders: 只保留通过风控的信号\n    if \"approved\" in approved.columns:\n        orders = approved[approved[\"approved\"].fillna(False)].copy()\n    else:\n        orders = approved.copy()\n\n    if \"target_weight\" in orders.columns:\n        orders[\"target_value\"] = orders[\"target_weight\"].fillna(0) * args.account_nav\n    else:\n        buy_rows = max(1, (orders[orders[\"signal_type\"] == \"BUY\"][\"ts_code\"].nunique() or 1))\n        default_value = args.available_cash / buy_rows\n        orders[\"target_value\"] = orders[\"signal_type\"].map(lambda x: default_value if x == \"BUY\" else 0)\n\n    orders[\"action\"] = orders[\"signal_type\"]\n    orders[\"reason\"] = orders.get(\"comment\", \"\")\n    orders[\"generated_at\"] = datetime.now().astimezone().isoformat()\n    orders[\"source_signal_file\"] = str(input_path)\n\n    keep_cols = [\n        \"trade_date\", \"ts_code\", \"action\", \"target_value\", \"target_weight\",\n        \"strategy_id\", \"score\", \"risk_adjustment\", \"risk_status\", \"reason\",\n        \"source_signal_file\", \"generated_at\", \"approved\",\n    ]\n    for col in keep_cols:\n        if col not in orders.columns:\n            orders[col] = None\n    orders = orders[keep_cols]\n\n    proposed_path = base / \"orders\" / \"proposed\" / f\"proposed_orders_{trade_tag}.csv\"\n    proposed_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    orders.to_csv(proposed_path, index=False)\n\n    print(f\"approved signals -> {approved_path}\")\n    print(f\"proposed orders -> {proposed_path}\")\n    approved_true = int(approved[\"approved\"].fillna(False).sum()) if \"approved\" in approved.columns else len(approved)\n    print(f\"rows: total={len(approved)}, approved={approved_true}, orders={len(orders)}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Apply risk engine to raw signals and emit approved signals + proposed orders.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport pandas as pd\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nif str(PROJECT_ROOT) not in sys.path:\n    sys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT))\n\nfrom risk.risk_engine import RiskConfig, RiskContext, RiskEngine\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    ap.add_argument(\"--input\", required=True, help=\"raw signal csv\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--trade-date\", required=True)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--account-nav\", type=float, default=1000000)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--available-cash\", type=float, default=1000000)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--market-breadth\", type=float, default=None)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--index-ret-pct\", type=float, default=None)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--strategy-max-dd-pct\", type=float, default=None)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--strategy-sharpe\", type=float, default=None)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--risk-off\", action=\"store_true\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--hard-stop\", action=\"store_true\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--risk-config\", type=str, default=None, help=\"path to risk config JSON\")\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    base = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(input_path)\n\n    raw = pd.read_csv(input_path)\n\n    if args.risk_config:\n        import json\n        with open(args.risk_config) as f:\n            cfg = json.load(f)\n        risk_config = RiskConfig(\n            max_total_exposure=cfg.get(\"max_total_exposure\", 1.0),\n            max_single_weight=cfg.get(\"max_single_weight\", 0.10),\n            riskoff_total_exposure=cfg.get(\"riskoff_total_exposure\", 0.65),\n            hard_stop_enabled=cfg.get(\"hard_stop_enabled\", True),\n            allow_new_buy_when_riskoff=cfg.get(\"allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\", False),\n            max_order_to_adv20_ratio=cfg.get(\"max_order_to_adv20_ratio\", 0.02),\n            index_halt_threshold_pct=cfg.get(\"index_halt_threshold_pct\"),\n            market_breadth_riskoff_threshold=cfg.get(\"market_breadth_riskoff_threshold\"),\n            market_breadth_hard_stop_threshold=cfg.get(\"market_breadth_hard_stop_threshold\"),\n            strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct=cfg.get(\"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\"),\n            strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold=cfg.get(\"strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold\"),\n            style_rotation_enabled=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_enabled\", False),\n            style_rotation_riskoff_short_excess_pct=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_riskoff_short_excess_pct\"),\n            style_rotation_riskoff_medium_excess_pct=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_riskoff_medium_excess_pct\"),\n            style_rotation_hard_stop_short_excess_pct=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_hard_stop_short_excess_pct\"),\n            style_rotation_hard_stop_medium_excess_pct=cfg.get(\"style_rotation_hard_stop_medium_excess_pct\"),\n            style_rotation_hard_stop_requires_negative_smallcap=cfg.get(\n                \"style_rotation_hard_stop_requires_negative_smallcap\",\n                True,\n            ),\n            blocked_codes=cfg.get(\"blocked_codes\", []),\n        )\n    else:\n        risk_config = RiskConfig(\n            max_total_exposure=1.0,\n            max_single_weight=0.10,\n            riskoff_total_exposure=0.65,\n            allow_new_buy_when_riskoff=False,\n        )\n\n    engine = RiskEngine(risk_config)\n    context = RiskContext(\n        trade_date=args.trade_date,\n        market_breadth=args.market_breadth,\n        risk_off=args.risk_off,\n        hard_stop=args.hard_stop,\n        available_cash=args.available_cash,\n        account_nav=args.account_nav,\n        index_ret_pct=args.index_ret_pct,\n        strategy_max_drawdown_pct=args.strategy_max_dd_pct,\n        strategy_sharpe=args.strategy_sharpe,\n    )\n\n    approved = engine.apply(raw, context)\n\n    trade_tag = args.trade_date.replace(\"-\", \"\")\n    approved_path = base / \"signals\" / \"approved\" / f\"approved_signals_{trade_tag}.csv\"\n    approved_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    approved.to_csv(approved_path, index=False)\n\n    # convert to proposed orders: 只保留通过风控的信号\n    if \"approved\" in approved.columns:\n        orders = approved[approved[\"approved\"].fillna(False)].copy()\n    else:\n        orders = approved.copy()\n\n    if \"target_weight\" in orders.columns:\n        orders[\"target_value\"] = orders[\"target_weight\"].fillna(0) * args.account_nav\n    else:\n        buy_rows = max(1, (orders[orders[\"signal_type\"] == \"BUY\"][\"ts_code\"].nunique() or 1))\n        default_value = args.available_cash / buy_rows\n        orders[\"target_value\"] = orders[\"signal_type\"].map(lambda x: default_value if x == \"BUY\" else 0)\n\n    orders[\"action\"] = orders[\"signal_type\"]\n    orders[\"reason\"] = orders.get(\"comment\", \"\")\n    orders[\"generated_at\"] = datetime.now().astimezone().isoformat()\n    orders[\"source_signal_file\"] = str(input_path)\n\n    keep_cols = [\n        \"trade_date\", \"ts_code\", \"action\", \"target_value\", \"target_weight\",\n        \"strategy_id\", \"score\", \"risk_adjustment\", \"risk_status\", \"reason\",\n        \"source_signal_file\", \"generated_at\", \"approved\",\n    ]\n    for col in keep_cols:\n        if col not in orders.columns:\n            orders[col] = None\n    orders = orders[keep_cols]\n\n    proposed_path = base / \"orders\" / \"proposed\" / f\"proposed_orders_{trade_tag}.csv\"\n    proposed_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    orders.to_csv(proposed_path, index=False)\n\n    print(f\"approved signals -> {approved_path}\")\n    print(f\"proposed orders -> {proposed_path}\")\n    approved_true = int(approved[\"approved\"].fillna(False).sum()) if \"approved\" in approved.columns else len(approved)\n    print(f\"rows: total={len(approved)}, approved={approved_true}, orders={len(orders)}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774083188033}}
{"type":"message","id":"368a37b0","parentId":"883b1262","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:53:08.047Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_mayH6C4lhchg0h9zyzuF9C5Q","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport math\nimport subprocess\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport pandas as pd\n\nfrom stock_analysis_decision_bridge import (  # type: ignore\n    EXECUTION_OVERLAY_PROFILE,\n    apply_stock_analysis_overlay,\n)\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nORDERS_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"orders\" / \"proposed\"\nSIGNALS_RAW_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"signals\" / \"raw\"\nSIGNALS_MERGED_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"signals\" / \"merged\"\nSIGNALS_APPROVED_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"signals\" / \"approved\"\nRISK_CONFIG_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / \"risk\" / \"configs\" / \"default_risk_config.json\"\nLIVE_TRADING_CONFIG_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / \"config\" / \"live_trading_v1.json\"\nA_STOCK_CSV = Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/data/a_stock_history.csv\")\n\nDEFAULT_ACCOUNT_NAV = 1000000.0\nDEFAULT_AVAILABLE_CASH = 1000000.0\nDEFAULT_LOT_SIZE = 100\nDEFAULT_LIVE_CANDIDATE_SETTINGS: dict[str, Any] = {\n    \"profile\": \"candidate_top50\",\n    \"config\": str(PROJECT_ROOT / \"config\" / \"strategy_smallcap_chip_candidate_top50.yaml\"),\n    \"main_count\": 10,\n    \"guard_count\": 8,\n    \"main_target_weight\": 0.10,\n    \"guard_target_weight\": 0.08,\n}\nDEFAULT_HEADER = [\n    \"ticket_time\",\n    \"ts_code\",\n    \"side\",\n    \"source_time\",\n    \"source_qty\",\n    \"source_price\",\n    \"source_amount\",\n    \"reason\",\n    \"confirm_status\",\n    \"execute_status\",\n    \"notes\",\n]\n\n\ndef parse_float(value: Any, default: float = 0.0) -> float:\n    try:\n        parsed = float(str(value).replace(\",\", \"\").strip())\n        return parsed if math.isfinite(parsed) else default\n    except Exception:\n        return default\n\n\ndef parse_int(value: Any, default: int = 0) -> int:\n    try:\n        return int(float(str(value).replace(\",\", \"\").strip()))\n    except Exception:\n        return default\n\n\ndef parse_bool(value: Any, default: bool = False) -> bool:\n    if value is None:\n        return default\n    text = str(value).strip().lower()\n    if text in {\"1\", \"true\", \"yes\", \"y\", \"ok\"}:\n        return True\n    if text in {\"0\", \"false\", \"no\", \"n\"}:\n        return False\n    return default\n\n\ndef normalize_side(value: Any) -> str:\n    text = str(value or \"\").strip().upper()\n    if text in {\"BUY\", \"SELL\"}:\n        return text\n    if any(k in text for k in [\"买\", \"BUY\", \"B\", \"LONG\"]):\n        return \"BUY\"\n    if any(k in text for k in [\"卖\", \"SELL\", \"S\", \"SHORT\"]):\n        return \"SELL\"\n    return \"\"\n\n\ndef normalize_joinquant_code(value: Any) -> str:\n    raw = str(value or \"\").strip().upper()\n    if not raw or raw == \"NAN\":\n        return \"\"\n    if raw.endswith(\".XSHG\") or raw.endswith(\".XSHE\"):\n        return raw\n    if raw.endswith(\".SH\"):\n        return raw[:-3] + \".XSHG\"\n    if raw.endswith(\".SZ\"):\n        return raw[:-3] + \".XSHE\"\n    if raw.startswith(\"SH\") and len(raw) >= 8:\n        return f\"{raw[2:8]}.XSHG\"\n    if raw.startswith(\"SZ\") and len(raw) >= 8:\n        return f\"{raw[2:8]}.XSHE\"\n    if raw.isdigit() and len(raw) == 6:\n        market = \"XSHG\" if raw.startswith((\"5\", \"6\", \"9\")) else \"XSHE\"\n        return f\"{raw}.{market}\"\n    return raw\n\n\ndef to_tushare_code(joinquant_code: str) -> str:\n    code = normalize_joinquant_code(joinquant_code)\n    if \".\" not in code:\n        return \"\"\n    symbol, market = code.split(\".\", 1)\n    if market == \"XSHG\":\n        return f\"{symbol}.SH\"\n    if market == \"XSHE\":\n        return f\"{symbol}.SZ\"\n    return \"\"\n\n\ndef count_csv_rows(path: Path) -> int:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return 0\n    try:\n        with path.open(\"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\", newline=\"\") as handle:\n            return max(0, sum(1 for _ in handle) - 1)\n    except Exception:\n        return 0\n\n\ndef ensure_parent(path: Path) -> None:\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n\ndef live_ticket_path(date_tag: str) -> Path:\n    return REPORT_DIR / f\"stock_signal_tickets_live_{date_tag}.csv\"\n\n\ndef legacy_ticket_path(date_tag: str) -> Path:\n    return REPORT_DIR / f\"stock_signal_tickets_{date_tag}.csv\"\n\n\ndef ticket_path(date_tag: str) -> Path:\n    return live_ticket_path(date_tag)\n\n\ndef summary_path(date_tag: str) -> Path:\n    return REPORT_DIR / f\"signal_ticket_bridge_summary_{date_tag}.json\"\n\n\ndef write_ticket_rows(path: Path, rows: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    ensure_parent(path)\n    frame = pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=DEFAULT_HEADER) if rows else pd.DataFrame(columns=DEFAULT_HEADER)\n    frame.to_csv(path, index=False, encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n\ndef write_summary(path: Path, payload: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n    ensure_parent(path)\n    path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n\ndef load_live_candidate_settings() -> dict[str, Any]:\n    settings = dict(DEFAULT_LIVE_CANDIDATE_SETTINGS)\n    if not LIVE_TRADING_CONFIG_PATH.exists():\n        return settings\n    try:\n        payload = json.loads(LIVE_TRADING_CONFIG_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    except Exception:\n        return settings\n\n    live_settings = payload.get(\"smallcap_live_candidates\", {}) or {}\n    if isinstance(live_settings, dict):\n        settings.update({k: v for k, v in live_settings.items() if v not in (None, \"\")})\n\n    config_value = str(settings.get(\"config\", \"\")).strip()\n    if config_value:\n        config_path = Path(config_value)\n        if not config_path.is_absolute():\n            config_path = (PROJECT_ROOT / config_path).resolve()\n        settings[\"config\"] = str(config_path)\n    return settings\n\n\ndef run_cmd(cmd: list[str], *, cwd: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    proc = subprocess.run(cmd, cwd=str(cwd), capture_output=True, text=True)\n    return {\n        \"cmd\": cmd,\n        \"returncode\": proc.returncode,\n        \"stdout\": (proc.stdout or \"\").strip(),\n        \"stderr\": (proc.stderr or \"\").strip(),\n    }\n\n\ndef materialize_signal_chain(date_tag: str, available_cash: float, account_nav: float, *, force_rebuild: bool = False) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    trade_date = f\"{date_tag[:4]}-{date_tag[4:6]}-{date_tag[6:8]}\"\n    ops: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    candidate_specs = [\n        (\n            REPORT_DIR / f\"manual_smallcap_candidates_{date_tag}.csv\",\n            PROJECT_ROOT / \"scripts\" / \"export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py\",\n            SIGNALS_RAW_DIR / f\"smallcap_chip_v4_2_{date_tag}.csv\",\n        ),\n        (\n            REPORT_DIR / f\"manual_smallcap_candidates_v4_2b_{date_tag}.csv\",\n            PROJECT_ROOT / \"scripts\" / \"export_smallcap_v4_2b_signal.py\",\n            SIGNALS_RAW_DIR / f\"smallcap_chip_v4_2b_{date_tag}.csv\",\n        ),\n    ]\n\n    missing_candidates = [\n        str(candidate_path)\n        for candidate_path, _, _ in candidate_specs\n        if force_rebuild or count_csv_rows(candidate_path) <= 0\n    ]\n    if missing_candidates:\n        auto_candidate_summary = REPORT_DIR / f\"live_smallcap_candidate_generation_{date_tag}.json\"\n        live_candidate_settings = load_live_candidate_settings()\n        cmd = [\n            \"python3\",\n            str(PROJECT_ROOT / \"scripts\" / \"generate_live_smallcap_candidates.py\"),\n            \"--date\",\n            date_tag,\n            \"--config\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"config\"]),\n            \"--main-count\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"main_count\"]),\n            \"--guard-count\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"guard_count\"]),\n            \"--main-target-weight\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"main_target_weight\"]),\n            \"--guard-target-weight\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"guard_target_weight\"]),\n            \"--summary-output\",\n            str(auto_candidate_summary),\n        ]\n        if force_rebuild:\n            cmd.append(\"--overwrite\")\n        op = run_cmd(cmd, cwd=PROJECT_ROOT)\n        op[\"step\"] = \"generate_live_candidates\"\n        op[\"missing_candidates\"] = missing_candidates\n        op[\"summary\"] = str(auto_candidate_summary)\n        op[\"live_candidate_settings\"] = live_candidate_settings\n        ops.append(op)\n\n    raw_paths: list[Path] = []\n    for candidate_path, script_path, output_path in candidate_specs:\n        if candidate_path.exists():\n            cmd = [\n                \"python3\",\n                str(script_path),\n                \"--input\",\n                str(candidate_path),\n                \"--trade-date\",\n                trade_date,\n                \"--output\",\n                str(output_path),"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport math\nimport subprocess\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport pandas as pd\n\nfrom stock_analysis_decision_bridge import (  # type: ignore\n    EXECUTION_OVERLAY_PROFILE,\n    apply_stock_analysis_overlay,\n)\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nORDERS_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"orders\" / \"proposed\"\nSIGNALS_RAW_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"signals\" / \"raw\"\nSIGNALS_MERGED_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"signals\" / \"merged\"\nSIGNALS_APPROVED_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"signals\" / \"approved\"\nRISK_CONFIG_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / \"risk\" / \"configs\" / \"default_risk_config.json\"\nLIVE_TRADING_CONFIG_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / \"config\" / \"live_trading_v1.json\"\nA_STOCK_CSV = Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/data/a_stock_history.csv\")\n\nDEFAULT_ACCOUNT_NAV = 1000000.0\nDEFAULT_AVAILABLE_CASH = 1000000.0\nDEFAULT_LOT_SIZE = 100\nDEFAULT_LIVE_CANDIDATE_SETTINGS: dict[str, Any] = {\n    \"profile\": \"candidate_top50\",\n    \"config\": str(PROJECT_ROOT / \"config\" / \"strategy_smallcap_chip_candidate_top50.yaml\"),\n    \"main_count\": 10,\n    \"guard_count\": 8,\n    \"main_target_weight\": 0.10,\n    \"guard_target_weight\": 0.08,\n}\nDEFAULT_HEADER = [\n    \"ticket_time\",\n    \"ts_code\",\n    \"side\",\n    \"source_time\",\n    \"source_qty\",\n    \"source_price\",\n    \"source_amount\",\n    \"reason\",\n    \"confirm_status\",\n    \"execute_status\",\n    \"notes\",\n]\n\n\ndef parse_float(value: Any, default: float = 0.0) -> float:\n    try:\n        parsed = float(str(value).replace(\",\", \"\").strip())\n        return parsed if math.isfinite(parsed) else default\n    except Exception:\n        return default\n\n\ndef parse_int(value: Any, default: int = 0) -> int:\n    try:\n        return int(float(str(value).replace(\",\", \"\").strip()))\n    except Exception:\n        return default\n\n\ndef parse_bool(value: Any, default: bool = False) -> bool:\n    if value is None:\n        return default\n    text = str(value).strip().lower()\n    if text in {\"1\", \"true\", \"yes\", \"y\", \"ok\"}:\n        return True\n    if text in {\"0\", \"false\", \"no\", \"n\"}:\n        return False\n    return default\n\n\ndef normalize_side(value: Any) -> str:\n    text = str(value or \"\").strip().upper()\n    if text in {\"BUY\", \"SELL\"}:\n        return text\n    if any(k in text for k in [\"买\", \"BUY\", \"B\", \"LONG\"]):\n        return \"BUY\"\n    if any(k in text for k in [\"卖\", \"SELL\", \"S\", \"SHORT\"]):\n        return \"SELL\"\n    return \"\"\n\n\ndef normalize_joinquant_code(value: Any) -> str:\n    raw = str(value or \"\").strip().upper()\n    if not raw or raw == \"NAN\":\n        return \"\"\n    if raw.endswith(\".XSHG\") or raw.endswith(\".XSHE\"):\n        return raw\n    if raw.endswith(\".SH\"):\n        return raw[:-3] + \".XSHG\"\n    if raw.endswith(\".SZ\"):\n        return raw[:-3] + \".XSHE\"\n    if raw.startswith(\"SH\") and len(raw) >= 8:\n        return f\"{raw[2:8]}.XSHG\"\n    if raw.startswith(\"SZ\") and len(raw) >= 8:\n        return f\"{raw[2:8]}.XSHE\"\n    if raw.isdigit() and len(raw) == 6:\n        market = \"XSHG\" if raw.startswith((\"5\", \"6\", \"9\")) else \"XSHE\"\n        return f\"{raw}.{market}\"\n    return raw\n\n\ndef to_tushare_code(joinquant_code: str) -> str:\n    code = normalize_joinquant_code(joinquant_code)\n    if \".\" not in code:\n        return \"\"\n    symbol, market = code.split(\".\", 1)\n    if market == \"XSHG\":\n        return f\"{symbol}.SH\"\n    if market == \"XSHE\":\n        return f\"{symbol}.SZ\"\n    return \"\"\n\n\ndef count_csv_rows(path: Path) -> int:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return 0\n    try:\n        with path.open(\"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\", newline=\"\") as handle:\n            return max(0, sum(1 for _ in handle) - 1)\n    except Exception:\n        return 0\n\n\ndef ensure_parent(path: Path) -> None:\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n\ndef live_ticket_path(date_tag: str) -> Path:\n    return REPORT_DIR / f\"stock_signal_tickets_live_{date_tag}.csv\"\n\n\ndef legacy_ticket_path(date_tag: str) -> Path:\n    return REPORT_DIR / f\"stock_signal_tickets_{date_tag}.csv\"\n\n\ndef ticket_path(date_tag: str) -> Path:\n    return live_ticket_path(date_tag)\n\n\ndef summary_path(date_tag: str) -> Path:\n    return REPORT_DIR / f\"signal_ticket_bridge_summary_{date_tag}.json\"\n\n\ndef write_ticket_rows(path: Path, rows: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    ensure_parent(path)\n    frame = pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=DEFAULT_HEADER) if rows else pd.DataFrame(columns=DEFAULT_HEADER)\n    frame.to_csv(path, index=False, encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n\ndef write_summary(path: Path, payload: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n    ensure_parent(path)\n    path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n\ndef load_live_candidate_settings() -> dict[str, Any]:\n    settings = dict(DEFAULT_LIVE_CANDIDATE_SETTINGS)\n    if not LIVE_TRADING_CONFIG_PATH.exists():\n        return settings\n    try:\n        payload = json.loads(LIVE_TRADING_CONFIG_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    except Exception:\n        return settings\n\n    live_settings = payload.get(\"smallcap_live_candidates\", {}) or {}\n    if isinstance(live_settings, dict):\n        settings.update({k: v for k, v in live_settings.items() if v not in (None, \"\")})\n\n    config_value = str(settings.get(\"config\", \"\")).strip()\n    if config_value:\n        config_path = Path(config_value)\n        if not config_path.is_absolute():\n            config_path = (PROJECT_ROOT / config_path).resolve()\n        settings[\"config\"] = str(config_path)\n    return settings\n\n\ndef run_cmd(cmd: list[str], *, cwd: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    proc = subprocess.run(cmd, cwd=str(cwd), capture_output=True, text=True)\n    return {\n        \"cmd\": cmd,\n        \"returncode\": proc.returncode,\n        \"stdout\": (proc.stdout or \"\").strip(),\n        \"stderr\": (proc.stderr or \"\").strip(),\n    }\n\n\ndef materialize_signal_chain(date_tag: str, available_cash: float, account_nav: float, *, force_rebuild: bool = False) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    trade_date = f\"{date_tag[:4]}-{date_tag[4:6]}-{date_tag[6:8]}\"\n    ops: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    candidate_specs = [\n        (\n            REPORT_DIR / f\"manual_smallcap_candidates_{date_tag}.csv\",\n            PROJECT_ROOT / \"scripts\" / \"export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py\",\n            SIGNALS_RAW_DIR / f\"smallcap_chip_v4_2_{date_tag}.csv\",\n        ),\n        (\n            REPORT_DIR / f\"manual_smallcap_candidates_v4_2b_{date_tag}.csv\",\n            PROJECT_ROOT / \"scripts\" / \"export_smallcap_v4_2b_signal.py\",\n            SIGNALS_RAW_DIR / f\"smallcap_chip_v4_2b_{date_tag}.csv\",\n        ),\n    ]\n\n    missing_candidates = [\n        str(candidate_path)\n        for candidate_path, _, _ in candidate_specs\n        if force_rebuild or count_csv_rows(candidate_path) <= 0\n    ]\n    if missing_candidates:\n        auto_candidate_summary = REPORT_DIR / f\"live_smallcap_candidate_generation_{date_tag}.json\"\n        live_candidate_settings = load_live_candidate_settings()\n        cmd = [\n            \"python3\",\n            str(PROJECT_ROOT / \"scripts\" / \"generate_live_smallcap_candidates.py\"),\n            \"--date\",\n            date_tag,\n            \"--config\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"config\"]),\n            \"--main-count\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"main_count\"]),\n            \"--guard-count\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"guard_count\"]),\n            \"--main-target-weight\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"main_target_weight\"]),\n            \"--guard-target-weight\",\n            str(live_candidate_settings[\"guard_target_weight\"]),\n            \"--summary-output\",\n            str(auto_candidate_summary),\n        ]\n        if force_rebuild:\n            cmd.append(\"--overwrite\")\n        op = run_cmd(cmd, cwd=PROJECT_ROOT)\n        op[\"step\"] = \"generate_live_candidates\"\n        op[\"missing_candidates\"] = missing_candidates\n        op[\"summary\"] = str(auto_candidate_summary)\n        op[\"live_candidate_settings\"] = live_candidate_settings\n        ops.append(op)\n\n    raw_paths: list[Path] = []\n    for candidate_path, script_path, output_path in candidate_specs:\n        if candidate_path.exists():\n            cmd = [\n                \"python3\",\n                str(script_path),\n                \"--input\",\n                str(candidate_path),\n                \"--trade-date\",\n                trade_date,\n                \"--output\",\n                str(output_path),","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774083188040}}
{"type":"message","id":"43c0b27b","parentId":"368a37b0","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:53:25.882Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Implementing a signal generator**\n\nI need to work on a quant project, specifically building a minimal mean reversion signal generator from scratch, along with an export script and some documentation. I'll likely run a smoke test and modify the active task via the command line as development progresses. It's crucial to commit only our new files since the git workspace is cluttered with unwanted changes. I need to implement files in the config and scripts areas, ensuring I don't alter the existing core pipeline.**Adding an exporter script**\n\nI'm considering adding an exporter script for the project. The implementation could include a configuration file for the strategy, a script to generate mean reversion signals, and another script for exporting those signals. I might also want to update the README or create a report. Running a smoke test will help ensure that the outputs are generated correctly using historical stock data. I can probably use PyYAML for parsing and keep everything self-contained with pandas.**Inspecting export scripts**\n\nI need to inspect the export_smallcap scripts to ensure the format is correct. It’s important to check for any inconsistencies or issues that might arise from the formatting before proceeding. I want to make sure that the output meets the standards required, as any discrepancies could lead to problems down the line. I'll take my time to go through them thoroughly to avoid any mistakes!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_sXnx044SlmYJfmh3GSRJEEG3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,220p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ZA9LFS9gOKAtUFIwOcT1oeyb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,220p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/export_smallcap_v4_2b_signal.py","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774083188050}}
{"type":"message","id":"d752e7c3","parentId":"43c0b27b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:53:25.951Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_sXnx044SlmYJfmh3GSRJEEG3","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Export normalized signal file for smallcap_chip_v4_2_alpha_recover.\n\n当前为主系统接入的第一版适配器：\n- 输入：人工/研究侧整理好的候选列表 CSV\n- 输出：标准化 signal CSV 到 signals/raw/\n\n输入 CSV 最低要求字段：\n- ts_code（或 code / symbol）\n可选字段：\n- score\n- target_weight\n- comment\n\n示例：\npython3 scripts/export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py \\\n  --input research/reports/manual_smallcap_candidates_20260310.csv \\\n  --trade-date 2026-03-10\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport pandas as pd\n\n\nSTRATEGY_ID = \"smallcap_chip_v4_2\"\n\n\ndef normalize_code(value: str) -> str:\n    v = str(value).strip()\n    if v.endswith((\".SZ\", \".SH\", \".BJ\")):\n        return v\n    if v.startswith((\"60\", \"68\")):\n        return f\"{v}.SH\"\n    if v.startswith((\"00\", \"30\")):\n        return f\"{v}.SZ\"\n    if v.startswith((\"8\", \"4\")):\n        return f\"{v}.BJ\"\n    return v\n\n\ndef resolve_code_column(df: pd.DataFrame) -> str:\n    for col in [\"ts_code\", \"code\", \"symbol\"]:\n        if col in df.columns:\n            return col\n    raise ValueError(\"Input CSV must contain one of: ts_code, code, symbol\")\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    ap.add_argument(\"--input\", required=True, help=\"candidate csv path\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--trade-date\", required=True, help=\"trade date, e.g. 2026-03-10\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--output\", default=None, help=\"output path; default signals/raw/{strategy_id}_{trade_date}.csv\")\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"input file not found: {input_path}\")\n\n    df = pd.read_csv(input_path)\n    code_col = resolve_code_column(df)\n\n    out = pd.DataFrame()\n    out[\"trade_date\"] = [args.trade_date] * len(df)\n    out[\"ts_code\"] = df[code_col].map(normalize_code)\n    out[\"signal_type\"] = \"BUY\"\n    out[\"score\"] = df[\"score\"] if \"score\" in df.columns else 1.0\n    out[\"target_weight\"] = df[\"target_weight\"] if \"target_weight\" in df.columns else None\n    out[\"strategy_id\"] = STRATEGY_ID\n    out[\"risk_flag\"] = \"normal\"\n    out[\"comment\"] = df[\"comment\"] if \"comment\" in df.columns else \"exported_from_candidate_list\"\n    out[\"source_run_id\"] = f\"{STRATEGY_ID}_{args.trade_date.replace('-', '')}\"\n    out[\"generated_at\"] = datetime.now().astimezone().isoformat()\n\n    out = out.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"trade_date\", \"ts_code\", \"strategy_id\"], keep=\"last\")\n\n    if args.output:\n        output_path = Path(args.output)\n    else:\n        base = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n        output_path = base / \"signals\" / \"raw\" / f\"{STRATEGY_ID}_{args.trade_date.replace('-', '')}.csv\"\n\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    out.to_csv(output_path, index=False)\n    print(f\"wrote {len(out)} rows -> {output_path}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Export normalized signal file for smallcap_chip_v4_2_alpha_recover.\n\n当前为主系统接入的第一版适配器：\n- 输入：人工/研究侧整理好的候选列表 CSV\n- 输出：标准化 signal CSV 到 signals/raw/\n\n输入 CSV 最低要求字段：\n- ts_code（或 code / symbol）\n可选字段：\n- score\n- target_weight\n- comment\n\n示例：\npython3 scripts/export_smallcap_v4_2_signal.py \\\n  --input research/reports/manual_smallcap_candidates_20260310.csv \\\n  --trade-date 2026-03-10\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport pandas as pd\n\n\nSTRATEGY_ID = \"smallcap_chip_v4_2\"\n\n\ndef normalize_code(value: str) -> str:\n    v = str(value).strip()\n    if v.endswith((\".SZ\", \".SH\", \".BJ\")):\n        return v\n    if v.startswith((\"60\", \"68\")):\n        return f\"{v}.SH\"\n    if v.startswith((\"00\", \"30\")):\n        return f\"{v}.SZ\"\n    if v.startswith((\"8\", \"4\")):\n        return f\"{v}.BJ\"\n    return v\n\n\ndef resolve_code_column(df: pd.DataFrame) -> str:\n    for col in [\"ts_code\", \"code\", \"symbol\"]:\n        if col in df.columns:\n            return col\n    raise ValueError(\"Input CSV must contain one of: ts_code, code, symbol\")\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    ap.add_argument(\"--input\", required=True, help=\"candidate csv path\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--trade-date\", required=True, help=\"trade date, e.g. 2026-03-10\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--output\", default=None, help=\"output path; default signals/raw/{strategy_id}_{trade_date}.csv\")\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"input file not found: {input_path}\")\n\n    df = pd.read_csv(input_path)\n    code_col = resolve_code_column(df)\n\n    out = pd.DataFrame()\n    out[\"trade_date\"] = [args.trade_date] * len(df)\n    out[\"ts_code\"] = df[code_col].map(normalize_code)\n    out[\"signal_type\"] = \"BUY\"\n    out[\"score\"] = df[\"score\"] if \"score\" in df.columns else 1.0\n    out[\"target_weight\"] = df[\"target_weight\"] if \"target_weight\" in df.columns else None\n    out[\"strategy_id\"] = STRATEGY_ID\n    out[\"risk_flag\"] = \"normal\"\n    out[\"comment\"] = df[\"comment\"] if \"comment\" in df.columns else \"exported_from_candidate_list\"\n    out[\"source_run_id\"] = f\"{STRATEGY_ID}_{args.trade_date.replace('-', '')}\"\n    out[\"generated_at\"] = datetime.now().astimezone().isoformat()\n\n    out = out.drop_duplicates(subset=[\"trade_date\", \"ts_code\", \"strategy_id\"], keep=\"last\")\n\n    if args.output:\n        output_path = Path(args.output)\n 