{"type":"message","id":"d1fba34b","parentId":"1085925c","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:55:40.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Implementing a trading strategy**\n\nI need to create a minimal viable implementation for a trading strategy. This involves setting up configurations and scripts for signal generation and exporting. I’ll also look into updating documentation and performing a smoke test using some available data files. The output will go into a processed data folder. I want to filter my universe based on stock codes and calculate features like moving average deviations and market regime classifications.**Combining scoring metrics**\n\nI need to create a scoring system that combines factors like a negative 5-day return, closing below the moving averages, intraday oversold conditions, rebound bounces, and possibly volume. The script should support either the latest date or the full historical data. For the overlay backtest, I’ll ensure to collect a time series with dates, instruments, and scores for all relevant dates to evaluate overall performance. I want to keep everything organized and clear!**Planning validation scripts**\n\nI'm considering a history analysis from 2015 onward. I could group by and compute useful metrics but might need to limit the data for a smoke test, perhaps focusing on the top N or a recent date range. Acceptance requires at least one runnable script and result validation. Running a recent range, maybe from the last 30 days, could work as a check-only overlay for file validation. I'll craft a design for necessary files and consider exporting raw signals as part of the smoke test.**Creating signal generation script**\n\nI'm planning to have a single script that generates both the RD factor and the latest raw signal. I think it simplifies the process by allowing outputs like a history factor file with useful columns and a raw output for recent trade dates. I'll ensure to normalize dates and filter out unnecessary index-like codes. My focus will be on handling codes that aren't relevant while only using the .SH/.SZ format in the data set for clearer execution of this task.**Planning data processing**\n\nI'm thinking about applying some methods that might be slower but still okay. Using `groupby` and `rolling` for the last few data points sounds good, but I'm concerned about memory issues with such a large file. Filtering the data by trade date to only include the last 2-3 years could help. If the file is around 2-3 GB, I'll need to be efficient with my approach. I might read in chunks to manage it better. Let's go with a chunk size of 500,000 and filter appropriately.**Considering data quality factors**\n\nI’m thinking about setting NaN for cases where there isn't enough historical data or if the quality fails. I have this boolean condition that checks if certain criteria are met, like if ret5 is less than or equal to -0.04. But, hmm, for the history factor, I wonder if I should be less strict since that might lead to sparse results. It’s a balancing act to ensure I’m getting meaningful data without losing too much.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qgBZ9QfFGiuMcGd1yoW3Qvow","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/active_task_cli.py","offset":1,"limit":260}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774083268528}}
{"type":"message","id":"d42400cd","parentId":"d1fba34b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:55:40.377Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_qgBZ9QfFGiuMcGd1yoW3Qvow","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport re\nimport sys\nimport tempfile\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nMETA_FIELDS = [\n    \"Status\",\n    \"Priority\",\n    \"Started\",\n    \"Updated\",\n    \"Workspace\",\n    \"Owner\",\n    \"User Trigger\",\n    \"Resume Entry\",\n]\n\nSECTION_FIELDS = [\n    \"Goal\",\n    \"Acceptance\",\n    \"Current\",\n    \"Next\",\n    \"Completed\",\n    \"Evidence\",\n    \"Blockers\",\n]\n\nSECTION_SET = set(SECTION_FIELDS)\nMETA_SET = set(META_FIELDS)\n\n\ndef normalize_item(value: str) -> str:\n    text = value.strip()\n    if not text:\n        return \"\"\n    return re.sub(r\"^[-*]\\s+\", \"\", text).strip()\n\n\ndef normalize_items(values: list[str]) -> list[str]:\n    items = [normalize_item(value) for value in values]\n    return [item for item in items if item and item.lower() != \"none\"]\n\n\ndef parse_active_task(path: Path) -> dict[str, object]:\n    text = path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    meta = {field: \"\" for field in META_FIELDS}\n    sections = {field: [] for field in SECTION_FIELDS}\n\n    current_section: str | None = None\n    for raw_line in text.splitlines():\n        line = raw_line.rstrip()\n        heading_match = re.match(r\"^##\\s+(.+?)\\s*$\", line)\n        if heading_match:\n            name = heading_match.group(1).strip()\n            current_section = name if name in SECTION_SET else None\n            continue\n\n        label_match = re.match(r\"^([A-Za-z][A-Za-z ]+):\\s*(.*)$\", line)\n        if label_match:\n            name = label_match.group(1).strip()\n            value = label_match.group(2).strip()\n            if name in META_SET:\n                meta[name] = value\n                current_section = None\n                continue\n            if name in SECTION_SET:\n                current_section = name\n                if value:\n                    sections[name].append(value)\n                continue\n\n        if current_section in SECTION_SET:\n            stripped = line.strip()\n            if stripped:\n                sections[current_section].append(stripped)\n\n    for key in sections:\n        sections[key] = normalize_items(sections[key])\n\n    return {\"meta\": meta, \"sections\": sections}\n\n\ndef render_active_task(state: dict[str, object]) -> str:\n    meta = state[\"meta\"]\n    sections = state[\"sections\"]\n\n    lines: list[str] = []\n    for field in META_FIELDS:\n        value = str(meta.get(field, \"\")).strip()\n        if value:\n            lines.append(f\"{field}: {value}\")\n    if lines:\n        lines.append(\"\")\n\n    for field in SECTION_FIELDS:\n        lines.append(f\"## {field}\")\n        items = normalize_items(list(sections.get(field, [])))\n        if items:\n            lines.extend(f\"- {item}\" for item in items)\n        else:\n            lines.append(\"- None\")\n        lines.append(\"\")\n\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines).rstrip() + \"\\n\"\n\n\ndef atomic_write(path: Path, content: str) -> None:\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(\n        \"w\",\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n        dir=path.parent,\n        delete=False,\n        prefix=f\".{path.name}.\",\n        suffix=\".tmp\",\n    ) as handle:\n        handle.write(content)\n        temp_path = Path(handle.name)\n    temp_path.replace(path)\n\n\ndef print_summary(path: Path, state: dict[str, object]) -> None:\n    meta = state[\"meta\"]\n    sections = state[\"sections\"]\n    payload = {\n        \"path\": str(path),\n        \"status\": meta.get(\"Status\", \"\"),\n        \"updated\": meta.get(\"Updated\", \"\"),\n        \"current\": sections.get(\"Current\", []),\n        \"next\": sections.get(\"Next\", []),\n        \"completed_count\": len(sections.get(\"Completed\", [])),\n        \"evidence_count\": len(sections.get(\"Evidence\", [])),\n        \"blockers\": sections.get(\"Blockers\", []),\n    }\n    print(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n\n\ndef cmd_show(args: argparse.Namespace) -> int:\n    path = Path(args.path).expanduser().resolve()\n    state = parse_active_task(path)\n    print_summary(path, state)\n    return 0\n\n\ndef cmd_advance(args: argparse.Namespace) -> int:\n    path = Path(args.path).expanduser().resolve()\n    state = parse_active_task(path)\n    meta = state[\"meta\"]\n    sections = state[\"sections\"]\n\n    current = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Current\", [])))\n    next_items = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Next\", [])))\n    completed = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Completed\", [])))\n    evidence = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Evidence\", [])))\n    blockers = normalize_items(list(sections.get(\"Blockers\", [])))\n\n    if args.complete_current:\n        completed.extend(current)\n        current = []\n\n    explicit_completed = normalize_items(list(args.complete or []))\n    if explicit_completed:\n        completed.extend(explicit_completed)\n        if current and any(item == current[0] for item in explicit_completed):\n            current = []\n\n    if args.append_completed:\n        completed.extend(normalize_items(list(args.append_completed)))\n\n    if args.append_evidence:\n        evidence.extend(normalize_items(list(args.append_evidence)))\n\n    if args.clear_blockers:\n        blockers = []\n    if args.set_blocker:\n        blockers = normalize_items(list(args.set_blocker))\n\n    if args.next is not None:\n        next_items = normalize_items(list(args.next))\n\n    if args.current and args.promote_next:\n        raise SystemExit(\"不能同时使用 --current 和 --promote-next\")\n\n    if args.current:\n        current = [normalize_item(args.current)]\n    elif args.promote_next:\n        if next_items:\n            current = [next_items[0]]\n            next_items = next_items[1:]\n        else:\n            current = []\n\n    if len(current) > 1:\n        raise SystemExit(\"Current 只能包含一个执行项\")\n\n    meta[\"Updated\"] = args.updated or datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M\")\n    if args.status:\n        meta[\"Status\"] = args.status\n\n    sections[\"Current\"] = current\n    sections[\"Next\"] = next_items\n    sections[\"Completed\"] = completed\n    sections[\"Evidence\"] = evidence\n    sections[\"Blockers\"] = blockers\n\n    content = render_active_task(state)\n    atomic_write(path, content)\n    verified = parse_active_task(path)\n    print_summary(path, verified)\n    return 0\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n        description=\"Read and atomically update ACTIVE_TASK.md.\",\n    )\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\n\n    show_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"show\", help=\"Print ACTIVE_TASK summary.\")\n    show_parser.add_argument(\"--path\", required=True, help=\"Path to ACTIVE_TASK.md\")\n    show_parser.set_defaults(func=cmd_show)\n\n    advance_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"advance\",\n        help=\"Atomically rewrite ACTIVE_TASK current/next/completed/evidence state.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\"--path\", required=True, help=\"Path to ACTIVE_TASK.md\")\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\"--status\", help=\"New Status value\")\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\"--updated\", help=\"Explicit Updated timestamp\")\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--complete-current\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        help=\"Move existing Current item into Completed before other updates.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--complete\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        help=\"Compatibility alias: append the provided item to Completed.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\"--current\", help=\"Set the new Current item\")\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--promote-next\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        help=\"Promote the first Next item into Current.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--next\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        help=\"Replace Next list; repeat for multiple items.\",\n    )\n    advance_parser.add_argument(\n        \"--append-completed\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        help=\"Append an item to Completed; repeat for multiple items.\",\n    )\n\n[29 more lines in file. Use offset=261 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774083340366}}
