{"type":"message","id":"d52af8f0","parentId":"70075d93","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:30:27.427Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's a `daily_basic_all_2019_2026.csv` which has fundamental data. Let me also check the `stock_analysis.db` which might have computed breadth. Actually, the best approach is to compute market breadth from the stock history data itself.Let me improve the script to compute real market breadth - the percentage of stocks above their 20-day moving average.","thinkingSignature":"2b67bee7cd29b77bb2f516a15261b5b42d596bd8a5bfbf5322b0a95978869804"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4uecwhk8vj03_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_day1_3_mean_reversion_signals.py","offset":100,"limit":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":62078,"output":154,"cacheRead":26949,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89181,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774085414310}}
{"type":"message","id":"07d057d5","parentId":"d52af8f0","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:30:27.465Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4uecwhk8vj03_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\ndef compute_market_gate(index_df: pd.DataFrame, trade_date: pd.Timestamp, cfg: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute market regime.\"\"\"\n    idx = index_df[index_df[\"date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    if len(idx) < 20:\n        return {\"regime\": \"neutral\", \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": 0.0, \"scale\": 0.6}\n    \n    idx[\"ma20\"] = idx[\"close\"].rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean()\n    latest_idx = idx.iloc[-1]\n    trend = float(latest_idx[\"close\"] / latest_idx[\"ma20\"] - 1.0) if pd.notna(latest_idx[\"ma20\"]) else 0.0\n    \n    strong_breadth = cfg.get(\"strong_breadth\", 0.58)\n    neutral_breadth = cfg.get(\"neutral_breadth\", 0.48)\n    weak_floor = cfg.get(\"weak_index_trend_floor\", -0.03)\n    \n    # For now, use neutral as default (breadth calculation needs more data)\n    if trend >= 0.02 and len(idx) > 60:\n        regime, scale = \"strong\", cfg.get(\"strong_scale\", 1.0)\n    elif trend >= weak_floor:\n        regime, scale = \"neutral\", cfg.get(\"neutral_scale\", 0.6)\n    else:\n        regime, scale = \"weak\", cfg.get(\"weak_scale\", 0.3)\n    \n    return {\"regime\": regime, \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": round(trend, 4), \"scale\": scale}\n\n\ndef main():\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Generate day1-3 mean reversion signals\")\n    ap.add_argument(\"--config\", default=str(DEFAULT_CONFIG))\n    ap.add_argument(\"--trade-date\", default=\"\", help=\"YYYY-MM-DD\")\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n    \n    cfg = load_yaml(Path(args.config).expanduser().resolve())\n    \n    # Determine target date\n    if args.trade_date:\n        target_date = args.trade_date\n    else:\n        hist_path = Path(cfg[\"history\"][\"csv\"]).expanduser()\n        dates = pd.read_csv(hist_path, usecols=[\"trade_date\"], dtype={\"trade_date\": str})\n        target_date = str(dates[\"trade_date\"].max())\n        target_date = f\"{target_date[:4]}-{target_date[4:6]}-{target_date[6:]}\"\n    \n    print(f\"Processing trade date: {target_date}\")\n    \n    # Load data\n    history = load_history(Path(cfg[\"history\"][\"csv\"]), target_date, 120)\n    print(f\"Loaded history: {len(history)} rows, {history['ts_code'].nunique()} stocks\")\n    \n    # Compute features\n    latest, actual_date = compute_features_for_date(history, target_date)\n    target_date = str(actual_date.date())\n    print(f\"Features computed: {len(latest)} stocks\")\n    \n    # Compute market gate\n    market_cfg = cfg[\"market\"]\n    index_df = pd.read_csv(Path(market_cfg[\"index_csv\"]).expanduser())\n    index_df[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(index_df[\"date\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    gate = compute_market_gate(index_df, actual_date, market_cfg)\n\n[138 more lines in file. Use offset=160 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774085427460}}
{"type":"message","id":"b52afb35","parentId":"07d057d5","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:30:51.109Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the current market gate logic is simplified - it doesn't compute real breadth. Let me improve it to compute real market breadth from the stock data. I'll:1. Pass the history dataframe to compute_market_gate\n2. Compute real breadth (% of stocks above their MA20)\n3. Use this for regime determinationLet me update the script.","thinkingSignature":"7110e0190de76774462ddc7640c809d07e17e2ff4ddfe1bfba781ccb2b0c2afe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bz8k9dgh8qv1_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_day1_3_mean_reversion_signals.py","oldText":"def compute_market_gate(index_df: pd.DataFrame, trade_date: pd.Timestamp, cfg: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute market regime.\"\"\"\n    idx = index_df[index_df[\"date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    if len(idx) < 20:\n        return {\"regime\": \"neutral\", \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": 0.0, \"scale\": 0.6}\n    \n    idx[\"ma20\"] = idx[\"close\"].rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean()\n    latest_idx = idx.iloc[-1]\n    trend = float(latest_idx[\"close\"] / latest_idx[\"ma20\"] - 1.0) if pd.notna(latest_idx[\"ma20\"]) else 0.0\n    \n    strong_breadth = cfg.get(\"strong_breadth\", 0.58)\n    neutral_breadth = cfg.get(\"neutral_breadth\", 0.48)\n    weak_floor = cfg.get(\"weak_index_trend_floor\", -0.03)\n    \n    # For now, use neutral as default (breadth calculation needs more data)\n    if trend >= 0.02 and len(idx) > 60:\n        regime, scale = \"strong\", cfg.get(\"strong_scale\", 1.0)\n    elif trend >= weak_floor:\n        regime, scale = \"neutral\", cfg.get(\"neutral_scale\", 0.6)\n    else:\n        regime, scale = \"weak\", cfg.get(\"weak_scale\", 0.3)\n    \n    return {\"regime\": regime, \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": round(trend, 4), \"scale\": scale}","newText":"def compute_market_gate(index_df: pd.DataFrame, history_df: pd.DataFrame, trade_date: pd.Timestamp, cfg: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute market regime with real breadth calculation.\"\"\"\n    # Get index trend\n    idx = index_df[index_df[\"date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    if len(idx) < 20:\n        return {\"regime\": \"neutral\", \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": 0.0, \"scale\": 0.6}\n    \n    idx[\"ma20\"] = idx[\"close\"].rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean()\n    latest_idx = idx.iloc[-1]\n    trend = float(latest_idx[\"close\"] / latest_idx[\"ma20\"] - 1.0) if pd.notna(latest_idx[\"ma20\"]) else 0.0\n    \n    # Compute REAL market breadth: % of stocks above their 20-day MA\n    # First compute MA20 for all stocks up to trade_date\n    hist = history_df[history_df[\"trade_date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    g = hist.groupby(\"ts_code\", group_keys=False)\n    hist[\"ma20_stock\"] = g[\"close\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean())\n    \n    # Get latest date data\n    latest = hist[hist[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date].copy()\n    latest = latest.dropna(subset=[\"ma20_stock\"])\n    \n    if len(latest) >= 50:  # Need enough stocks for meaningful breadth\n        breadth = float((latest[\"close\"] > latest[\"ma20_stock\"]).mean())\n    else:\n        breadth = 0.5  # Default if not enough data\n    \n    strong_breadth = cfg.get(\"strong_breadth\", 0.58)\n    neutral_breadth = cfg.get(\"neutral_breadth\", 0.48)\n    weak_floor = cfg.get(\"weak_index_trend_floor\", -0.03)\n    \n    # Determine regime based on BOTH trend AND breadth\n    if breadth >= strong_breadth and trend >= 0:\n        regime, scale = \"strong\", cfg.get(\"strong_scale\", 1.0)\n    elif breadth >= neutral_breadth and trend >= weak_floor:\n        regime, scale = \"neutral\", cfg.get(\"neutral_scale\", 0.6)\n    else:\n        regime, scale = \"weak\", cfg.get(\"weak_scale\", 0.3)\n    \n    return {\"regime\": regime, \"breadth\": round(breadth, 4), \"trend\": round(trend, 4), \"scale\": scale}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":62967,"output":1062,"cacheRead":26949,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90978,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774085427466}}
{"type":"message","id":"f048b749","parentId":"b52afb35","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:30:51.169Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bz8k9dgh8qv1_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_day1_3_mean_reversion_signals.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  98     \n  99     return latest, trade_date\n 100 \n 101 \n-102 def compute_market_gate(index_df: pd.DataFrame, trade_date: pd.Timestamp, cfg: dict) -> dict:\n-103     \"\"\"Compute market regime.\"\"\"\n+102 def compute_market_gate(index_df: pd.DataFrame, history_df: pd.DataFrame, trade_date: pd.Timestamp, cfg: dict) -> dict:\n+103     \"\"\"Compute market regime with real breadth calculation.\"\"\"\n+104     # Get index trend\n 104     idx = index_df[index_df[\"date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n 105     if len(idx) < 20:\n 106         return {\"regime\": \"neutral\", \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": 0.0, \"scale\": 0.6}\n 107     \n 108     idx[\"ma20\"] = idx[\"close\"].rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean()\n 109     latest_idx = idx.iloc[-1]\n 110     trend = float(latest_idx[\"close\"] / latest_idx[\"ma20\"] - 1.0) if pd.notna(latest_idx[\"ma20\"]) else 0.0\n 111     \n+113     # Compute REAL market breadth: % of stocks above their 20-day MA\n+114     # First compute MA20 for all stocks up to trade_date\n+115     hist = history_df[history_df[\"trade_date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n+116     g = hist.groupby(\"ts_code\", group_keys=False)\n+117     hist[\"ma20_stock\"] = g[\"close\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean())\n+118     \n+119     # Get latest date data\n+120     latest = hist[hist[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date].copy()\n+121     latest = latest.dropna(subset=[\"ma20_stock\"])\n+122     \n+123     if len(latest) >= 50:  # Need enough stocks for meaningful breadth\n+124         breadth = float((latest[\"close\"] > latest[\"ma20_stock\"]).mean())\n+125     else:\n+126         breadth = 0.5  # Default if not enough data\n+127     \n 112     strong_breadth = cfg.get(\"strong_breadth\", 0.58)\n 113     neutral_breadth = cfg.get(\"neutral_breadth\", 0.48)\n 114     weak_floor = cfg.get(\"weak_index_trend_floor\", -0.03)\n 115     \n-116     # For now, use neutral as default (breadth calculation needs more data)\n-117     if trend >= 0.02 and len(idx) > 60:\n+132     # Determine regime based on BOTH trend AND breadth\n+133     if breadth >= strong_breadth and trend >= 0:\n 118         regime, scale = \"strong\", cfg.get(\"strong_scale\", 1.0)\n-119     elif trend >= weak_floor:\n+135     elif breadth >= neutral_breadth and trend >= weak_floor:\n 120         regime, scale = \"neutral\", cfg.get(\"neutral_scale\", 0.6)\n 121     else:\n 122         regime, scale = \"weak\", cfg.get(\"weak_scale\", 0.3)\n 123     \n-124     return {\"regime\": regime, \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": round(trend, 4), \"scale\": scale}\n+140     return {\"regime\": regime, \"breadth\": round(breadth, 4), \"trend\": round(trend, 4), \"scale\": scale}\n 125 \n 126 \n 127 def main():\n 128     ap = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Generate day1-3 mean reversion signals\")\n     ...","firstChangedLine":102},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774085451158}}
