{"type":"message","id":"237333f4","parentId":"813e7ece","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:53:52.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems only 2026 files were generated - the same 30 files. The background process ran but it seems like only the same dates were processed (2026-01-29 to 2026-03-20). That's because the earlier dates in 2024-2025 may not have data or the script might have failed on those earlier dates due to missing historical data.\n\nLooking at the history data range, it only starts from 2015 but the data might be sparse for earlier years. The original data we loaded was cut off at 2025-01 because the data file is truncated.\n\nLet me check what's happening - maybe the data before 2026 doesn't exist or has issues. But actually, from the earlier check we saw:```\nTotal dates: 2722\nDate range: 20150105 to 20260319```\n\nSo there should be data from 2015 onwards. But the issue is that the script is slow and the batch processing might have timed out or had issues.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, the background process output showed it completed all 11 batches. But maybe the script didn't process older dates properly. Let me try running the factor generation for just a few 2024 dates to debug.","thinkingSignature":"8d64d3da4fa9278053cf47cdbcb7ecc4220605ea61013407f5f1f1acbf854551"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_okcdu6zntb9z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_day1_3_mean_reversion_signals.py --trade-date 2024-01-02 2>&1 | tail -10","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":116862,"output":347,"cacheRead":41408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":158617,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774090423897}}
